I don't understand the hype of this store.
Upon walking in, there was a strong scent of room spray.
I'm all for anything that smells girly and floral but this scent....it was overpowering and within a few minutes, it made my throat dry and scratchy =/  Having the store drenched in a strong scent is fine as long as the clothes/accessories make up for it but it didn't even come close.
The quality of the jewelry looks and feels cheap, but yet they were charging a necklace I can find at forever21 for $8.80 at a selling price for about $13-20.
The clothing style looked grandma-ish...if that makes sense.
=/ It was either grandma style or if you were starring in a role for Rock of Ages musical.
I came, I saw, I'm not coming back.
Sorry....

